      "facility": "Austin Orthopedic Center", "place_of_service": "11",
      "clinical_note": "Patient is a 65-year-old male presenting with worsening right knee pain x 6 months. Reports failed conservative treatment including 12 weeks of physical therapy (completed 11/2023), NSAIDs (ibuprofen 800mg TID x 3 months with minimal relief), and corticosteroid injection (administered 10/2023 with temporary 2-week improvement). X-ray shows Kellgren-Lawrence Grade IV osteoarthritis with bone-on-bone changes. ROM: flexion 90 degrees (limited), extension -10 degrees. Valgus deformity noted. BMI 29.2. Patient is medically optimized for surgery. Recommend total knee arthroplasty. Prior authorization to be submitted to UHC."
    },
