      "clinical_note": "57-year-old male presents to ED with acute onset chest pain radiating to left arm x 2 hours. Diaphoretic, BP 178/95, HR 98, SpO2 97%. ECG: ST elevations in leads II, III, aVF. Troponin I: 2.4 ng/mL (elevated). Diagnosis: STEMI inferior wall. Heparin bolus given, loaded with aspirin and clopidogrel. Emergent cardiac catheterization arranged. Cardiology consulted."
