      "clinical_note": "43-year-old female with chronic low back pain radiating to right leg x 8 months. Failed 12 weeks PT, NSAIDs (naproxen, meloxicam), muscle relaxants. MRI lumbar spine 01/2024: L4-L5 right paracentral disc herniation with moderate foraminal stenosis and right L5 nerve root compression. Positive straight leg raise on right at 40 degrees. Motor: 4/5 right EHL. Recommend right L4-L5 transforaminal epidural steroid injection. This is her first injection this year."
    },
    {
